Description of gonopod . Slightly curved towards cephalic side on caudo-mesial view, narrower at end of proximal third. Marginal suture on mesial surface, not distorted to other surfaces. Distal portion of caudo-marginal projection unilobate, with slightly convex outline in mesial view. Marginal process (cephalic end of caudomarginal projection, sensu
Villalobos & Alvarez, 2010
) rounded, not produced beyond the mesial crest of apex. Mesial process weakly developed, as short, rounded protuberance. Distocaudal ridge elongated, extending distally from beginning of the second third of stem length. Apex elongated, narrow; mesial crest nearly straight, lateral crest slightly concave in apical view, both crests slightly convex in mesial view. Apex cavity situated distally, with both spermatic channel opening, field of apical spines positioned towards cephalic end; field of apical spines weakly developed.

Distribution . Central Costa Rica , Atlantic drainage (
Fig. 77
).
